{{Infobox person | name = Sheeri Kritzer Cabral | image = Sheeri Cabral 2012.jpg | image_size = 150px | caption = Cabral in 2012 | birth_name = Sheeri Kritzer | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1978|9|17}} | birth_place = Ridgewood, NJ | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = Boston, MA | nationality = United States | other_names = | education = [[Brandeis University]] | occupation = Senior DBA | known_for = [[MySQL]] | salary = | height = 5 ft 3 in | weight = | title = Database Administrator/Architect | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | spouse = [http://www.bostoncardshark.com Tony Cabral] 2007- | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | website = [http://sheeri.com/ Sheeri dot com] | signature = | footnotes = | networth = }}
'''Sheeri Cabral''' (born 17 September 1978), née Kritzer, is a [[MySQL]] community contributor. She was chosen as the first<ref name="pythian">{{cite web|url=http://www.pythian.com/news/10643/meet-the-first-oracle-ace-director-in-mysql-sheeri-cabral/|title=Meet the First Oracle ACE Director in MySQL -- Sheeri Cabral|publisher=pythian.com|accessdate=2014-10-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113052944/http://www.pythian.com/news/10643/meet-the-first-oracle-ace-director-in-mysql-sheeri-cabral/#|archive-date=2012-11-13|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> [[Oracle Corporation|Oracle]] ACE Director for MySQL.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.oracle.com/otn/2010/04/welcome_oracle_ace_directors_f |accessdate=2010-05-08 |df= }}{{dead link|date=June 2018|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}} </ref> She won the MySQL Community Advocate, Communicator and Facilitator award in 2007<ref name="mysql">{{cite web|url=http://planet.mysql.com/kaj/?p=107|title=Planet MySQL|publisher=planet.mysql.com|accessdate=2014-10-24}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and again in 2008<ref name="mysql2">{{cite web|url=http://blogs.mysql.com/kaj/2008/04/15/mysql-community-awards-2008/|title=Planet MySQL|publisher=blogs.mysql.com|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> for her frequent blog posts, community work, and conference/user group presentations;<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20161014182706/http://www.sheeri.com/resume/#presentations] </ref> this sparked a keynote presentation for the 2009 MySQL User Conference & Expo on "How to be a Community Superhero".<ref name="mysqlconf">{{cite web|url=http://www.mysqlconf.com/mysql2009/public/schedule/detail/9098|title=O&#x27;Reilly MySQL Conference &amp; Expo 2011 - O&#x27;Reilly Conferences, April 11 - 14, 2011, Santa Clara, CA|publisher=mysqlconf.com|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> She delivered another community keynote entitled, "Under New Management: Next Steps for the Community" <ref name="oreilly">{{cite web|url=http://en.oreilly.com/mysql2010/public/schedule/detail/14808|title=Under New Management: Next Steps for the Community: O&#x27;Reilly MySQL Conference &amp; Expo 2010 - O&#x27;Reilly Conferences, April 12 - 15, 2010, Santa Clara, CA|publisher=en.oreilly.com|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> at the same conference in 2010. In 2012, she won the MySQL Community Award again <ref name="openlife">{{cite web|url=http://openlife.cc/blogs/2012/april/mysql-community-awards-2012-and-winners-are|title=MySQL Community Awards 2012: And the winners are... &#124; OpenLife.cc|publisher=openlife.cc|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> for her work founding and co-hosting the OurSQL podcast.
Cabral wrote the ''MySQL Administrator's Bible'',<ref name="wiley">{{cite web|url=http://www.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0470416912.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081202120913/http://www.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0470416912.html|archive-date=2008-12-02|dead-url=yes|title=Wiley: MySQL Administrator's Bible - Sheeri K. Cabral, Keith Murphy|accessdate=2014-10-24|df=}}</ref> and has edited the [[O'Reilly Media|O'Reilly]] books ''SQL Hacks<ref name="scribd">{{cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/doc/15490480/SQL-Hacks-by-OReilly-Media|title=SQL Hacks|publisher=scribd.com|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref>''(2007), ''High Performance MySQL 2nd edition<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/doc/15490578/High-Performance-MySQL-by-OReilly-Media|title=High Performance MySQL : Optimization, Backups, Replication, and More by Schwartz Schwartz, Peter Zaitsev, and Vadim Tkachenko - Read Online|publisher=|accessdate=10 April 2018}}</ref>''(2008), and [[Christopher J. Date|C.J. Date]]'s ''How to Write Accurate SQL Code''.<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=SQL and Relational Theory: How to Write Accurate SQL Code|author=Date, C.J.|date=2009|publisher=O'Reilly Media|isbn=9780596555429|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=406_pJtiJ6sC|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> Cabral developed a new version of mysqltuner<ref name="launchpad">{{cite web|url=http://www.launchpad.net/mysqltuner|title=mysqltuner in Launchpad|publisher=launchpad.net|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> (with permission from Major Hayden for the name), which led to developing the mysql_health check Nagios plugin.<ref name="nagiosplugin">{{cite web|url=https://exchange.nagios.org/directory/Plugins/Databases/MySQL/mysql_health_check/details|title=plugin at Nagios Exchange|publisher=nagios.org}}</ref>
Cabral has a master's degree in Computer Science from [[Brandeis University]] and is MySQL 5.0 DBA Certified and MySQL Core Certified.<ref name="sheeri">{{cite web|url=http://sheeri.com/content/testimonials|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080410071133/http://sheeri.com/content/testimonials|archive-date=2008-04-10|dead-url=yes|title=Testimonials &#124; Sheeri dot com|accessdate=2014-10-24|df=}}</ref>
==Other notable work== *Program Committee Member for the Open Source Convention (OSCon) for 2011 and 2012<ref name="oreilly2">{{cite web|url=http://en.oreilly.com/oscon2011/public/content/about|title=About: OSCON 2011 - O&#x27;Reilly Conferences, July 25 - 29, 2011, Portland, OR|publisher=En.oreilly.com|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> *IOUG MySQL Council Member, 2011–present<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110312044010/http://www.ioug.org/portals/0/MySQL_Council_release.docx] </ref> *MySQL Track Manager for Collaborate 2011<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20100913061127/http://www.ioug.org/Events/IOUGWelcomesMySQL/tabid/164/Default.aspx#624] </ref> *Organizer of OpenSQLCamp Boston<ref>{{cite web|url=http://opensqlcamp.org/Events/Boston2010/|title=White Pages Goes Green by Yellow Pages Directory Inc - Yellow Pages Goes Green ® 2018|website=Opensqlcamp.org|accessdate=10 April 2018}}</ref> *Program Committee Member for the 2010 MySQL User Conference & Expo<ref name="oreilly3">{{cite web|url=http://en.oreilly.com/mysql2010/public/content/about#program-chair|title=About: O&#x27;Reilly MySQL Conference &amp; Expo 2010 - O&#x27;Reilly Conferences, April 12 - 15, 2010, Santa Clara, CA|publisher=en.oreilly.com|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> *Organizer of the 2009 MySQL Camp<ref name="sun">[https://web.archive.org/web/20090203192906/http://blogs.sun.com/datacharmer/entry/mysql_users_conference_with_embedded] </ref> *Boston MySQL User Group Founder and frequent speaker<ref name="meetup">{{cite web|url=http://meetup.com/mysqlbos|title=The Boston MySQL Meetup Group (Boston, MA) - Meetup|publisher=Meetup.com|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> *Technocation, Inc Founder and Treasurer 2004–2017<ref name="technocation">{{cite web|url=http://www.technocation.org|title=Technocation, Inc.|publisher=Technocation.org|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> *Volunteer DBA work for The Human Creativity Project<ref name="humancreativity">{{cite web|url=http://www.humancreativity.com/who.html|title=the human creativity project : Who|publisher=Humancreativity.com|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref> *MySQL Podcast ("OurSQL"), November 2006 – February 2009, December 2010 – June 2015 (founder and co-host to over 200 episodes)<ref name="apple">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewPodcast?id=206806301&subMediaType=Audio|title=iTunes Store|publisher=itunes.apple.com|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref><ref name="technocation2">{{cite web|url=http://technocation.org/audio/feed|title=OurSQL: MySQL Database Community Podcast|publisher=Technocation.org|accessdate=2014-10-24}}</ref>
Cabral has worked as a Systems Administrator for [[Tufts University]]; a Database Administrator for [[Guardium, an IBM Company|Guardium, Inc]], [[Manhunt.net]] and [[Pythian Group|The Pythian Group]], a Database Operations Manager for PalominoDB, Inc., and a Senior Database Administrator/Architect, then Data Team Manager at [[Mozilla Corporation|Mozilla]]. She currently works as a Senior Database Administrator for [[Salesforce]] .
